<paragraph blockId="5.[340,1248,562,643]" pageId="5">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Large species, 
<quantity box="[719,796,562,584]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
(abdomen fully extended). Coloration: head blackish; pronotum and elytra reddish brown; abdomen blackish, with the apex and segments 
<collectionCode box="[440,500,622,643]" pageId="5">III-IV</collectionCode>
slightly paler; legs testaceous; antennae dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[340,1248,658,739]" pageId="5">
Facies as in 
<figureCitation box="[472,549,658,680]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
. Head and pronotum with shallow fine microreticulation (
<figureCitation box="[1157,1235,658,680]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Eyes moderately small, weakly protruding from lateral outline of head, slightly less than half the length of postocular region in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5434900" box="[340,1248,1630,1650]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5" startId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" targetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[340,1248,1630,1718]" box="[340,1248,1630,1650]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[340,439,1630,1650]" pageId="5">Figs 13-19</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Homson, 1974" authorityName="Homson" authorityYear="1974" box="[452,595,1630,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anlasi" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[452,595,1630,1650]" italics="true" pageId="5">Geostiba anlasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[601,645,1630,1650]" pageId="5" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(holotype): (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[765,788,1630,1650]" pageId="5">13</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[911,934,1630,1650]" pageId="5">14</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1074,1097,1630,1650]" pageId="5">15</emphasis>
) anterior part of
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[340,1248,1630,1718]" pageId="5">
abdomen; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[473,496,1653,1673]" pageId="5">16</emphasis>
) right elytron in lateral view; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[820,843,1653,1673]" pageId="5">17</emphasis>
) tergite VIII; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1014,1037,1653,1673]" pageId="5">18</emphasis>
) sternite VIII; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1217,1240,1653,1673]" pageId="5">19</emphasis>
) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13: 1.0 mm; 14-15: 
<quantity box="[1019,1093,1676,1696]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
; 16-18: 
<quantity box="[1170,1244,1676,1696]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
; 19: 
<quantity box="[375,447,1698,1718]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[340,1248,1733,1813]" pageId="5">
Pronotum apparently without appreciable sexual dimorphism, distinctly convex in crosssection, approximately 1.15 times as wide as head and 1.05 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1236,1762,1784]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Elytra with pronounced sexual dimorphism, approximately 0.55 times as long as pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[770,818,357,378]" box="[770,818,357,378]" pageId="6">1185</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[340,1248,431,600]" pageId="6">
Abdomen rather shining; puncturation relatively sparse and fine on anterior tergites, very sparse and very fine on posterior tergites; microsculpture on tergites VI-VII very shallow, barely noticeable, on tergites III-V obsolete; segment III conspicuously elongated, ratio of width (across posterior margin) and length (from anterior margin of paratergite to posterior margin of tergite): 1.23 (
<figureCitation box="[707,787,549,571]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of tergite 
<collectionCode box="[1101,1136,549,570]" pageId="6">VII</collectionCode>
with very indistinct narrow rudiment of a palisade fringe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[340,1248,616,815]" pageId="6">
: elytra with ill-defined, somewhat granulose puncturation (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1083,616,638]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); laterally with pronounced (long and strongly elevated, especially posteriorly) fold (
<figureCitation box="[1081,1162,646,668]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); suture slightly elevated (
<figureCitation box="[521,597,675,697]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites III-V without tubercles; tergite 
<collectionCode box="[1129,1164,676,697]" pageId="6">VII</collectionCode>
without process; tergite VIII highly distinctive: posterior margin with pair of pronounced processes (
<figureCitation box="[418,494,734,756]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[701,776,734,756]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
; median lobe of aedeagus with dagger-shaped cristal process (
<figureCitation box="[510,591,763,785]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); apical lobe of paramere shaped as in other species of the subgenus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[361,476,830,852]" box="[361,476,830,852]" pageId="6">: unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[340,1248,868,919]" pageId="6">
E t y m o l o g y: This remarkable species is dedicated to Sinan Anlaú, 
<collectingRegion box="[1130,1187,868,890]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="6">Izmir</collectingRegion>
, who discovered the 
<typeStatus box="[493,585,897,919]" pageId="6">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[340,1248,934,1015]" pageId="6">C o m m e n t: The question whether the conspicuously long abdominal segment III is a character shared by both sexes or confined to males can be clarified only when females become available for examination.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[340,1248,1030,1169]" pageId="6">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: This highly distinctive species is easily identified among its congeners by several unique characters: the morphology of the male elytra (pronounced lateral folds, absence of pronounced sutural carinae), the elongated abdominal segment III, the absence of a process on the male tergite 
<collectionCode box="[1027,1064,1119,1140]" pageId="6">VII</collectionCode>
, and the shape of the male tergite VIII with a pair of pronounced processes at the posterior margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[340,1248,1184,1580]" pageId="6">
In order to account for this species, the key in 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[810,971,1184,1207]" pageId="6" pagination="903 - 1006" refId="ref20419" refString="ASSING V. (2005 a): A revision of the species of Geostiba THOMSON and Tropimenelytron PACE of the Eastern Mediterranean, the Caucasus, and adjacent regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biol. Beitr. 37 (2): 903 - 1006." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING (2005a)</bibRefCitation>
is modified as follows: 107 Abdominal segment III conspicuously elongated, ratio of width (across posterior margin) and length (from anterior margin of paratergite to posterior margin of tergite): &lt;1.3 (
<figureCitation box="[566,642,1263,1284]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).: elytra with pronounced lateral folds (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1209,1263,1284]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figs 14, 16</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of tergite VIII with pair of pronounced processes (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1208,1285,1306]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); median lobe of aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[712,783,1308,1329]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
. Western 
<collectingCountry box="[878,965,1308,1329]" name="Turkey" pageId="6">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[974,1116,1308,1329]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="6">Izmir province</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1129,1193,1308,1329]" captionStart="Map 3" captionStartId="10.[340,385,1651,1671]" captionTargetBox="[340,1254,1088,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[340,1254,1088,1640]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Map 3: Distributions of Geostiba nifica (black circles), G. atromontis (white circles), G. aydinica (grey circles), G. anlasi (large black square), G. biformis (small black squares), and G. renneri (white square) in western and southwestern Anatolia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434908/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Map 3</figureCitation>
